== 内容 ==
直到十九世纪中叶，英国和爱尔兰的商业银行依然能够发现自己的纸币，省级银行业公司的银行券在流通中更是随处可见。<ref>{{cite web|title=£2 note issued by Evans, Jones, Davies & Co.|url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/cm/others/%c2%a32_note_issued_by_evans,_jones.aspx|accessdate=31 October 2011|publisher=British Museum|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118104053/http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/cm/others/%c2%a32_note_issued_by_evans,_jones.aspx|archive-date=2012-01-18|url-status=dead}}</ref>

根据法令，除了英格兰银行外，其他银行不得发行新的[[纸币|纸币]]（银行券），现有发行纸币的银行如果破产倒闭，则需收回其发行的纸币；与此同时，英格兰银行若发行新币，则需有全额黄金为保证。法令起到了限制流通中纸币供应量的作用，也让英格兰银行有效垄断了新币的发行。不过，活期存款却不受法令的约束，与纸币不同，无需以全额黄金为保证。<ref>{{cite web|title=昨天是一个历史性的日子|url=http://blog.mises.org/13920/yesterday-was-a-historic-day/|accessdate=2010-09-17|date=|publisher=米塞斯研究院博客|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100918034732/http://blog.mises.org/13920/yesterday-was-a-historic-day/|archive-date=2010-09-18|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

此法令将[[金银本位主义|金银本位主义]]在[[英国|英国]]制度化，<ref>Anna Gambles, ''Protection and Politics: Conservative Economic Discourse, 1815-1852'' (Royal Historical Society/Boydell Press, 1999), pp. 117-18.</ref>规定了[[英格兰银行|英格兰银行]]的黄金储备和可发行钞票之间的比率<ref name="Poovey">{{cite book|first=Mary|last=Poovey|author-link=|title=Genres of the Credit Economy: Mediating Value in Eighteenth- and Nineteenth-Century Britain|publisher=University of Chicago Press|date=2008|page=49}}</ref>，将[[英格兰|英格兰]]和[[威爾斯|威爾斯]]的银行可发行的没有黄金储备支持的钞票限制在1400万[[英镑|英镑]]内。<ref>{{cite book|first=Peter|last=Dewey|title=War and Progress: Britain 1914-1945|orig-year=1994|date=2014|publisher=Routledge|page=74}}</ref>法令严格限制了国内各大银行的发钞权，<ref name="Poovey" />阻止[[英国|英国]]任何其他银行获得钞票发行权，开始了钞票发行中央集权化的进程。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bank Charter Act 1844: No banker not issuing notes on 6th May 1844, to issue notes hereafter|url=https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/Vict/7-8/32/section/10|date=19 July 1844|year=1844|website=legislation.gov.uk|publisher=The National Archives (United Kingdom)|quote=No person other than a banker who on the sixth day of May one thousand eight hundred and forty-four was lawfully issuing his own bank notes shall make or issue bank notes in any part of the United Kingdom.|id=(7 and 8 Vict) c.32 (s. 10)|access-date=2022-04-10|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120175559/https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/Vict/7-8/32/section/10}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{cite book|first1=Gianni|last1=Tonilo|first2=Eugene N.|last2=White|chapter=The Evolution of the Financial Stability Mandate: From Its Origin to the Present Day|title=Central Banks at a Crossroads|publisher=Cambridge University Press|date=2016|page=431}}</ref>

== 影响 ==
虽然法令要求新币必须以黄金或[[公债|公债]]为全额保证，不过却给了政府在发生金融危机时候暂时停止黄金支付的权力，而在历史上也确实发生过数次政府暂停支付黄金的事件，分别发生在1847年、1857年和1866年[[欧沃伦格尼银行|欧沃伦格尼银行]]（Overend Gurney Bank）危机期间。同时，尽管法令限制了新币的发行，却并没有限制银行凭空创造新的[[存款|存款]]，在十九世纪后半叶，这些存款会继续增加货币的供应量。<ref name=":0" />

储户办理储蓄业务时，银行向客户借债，许诺带息返还，并允以可观的抵押物，银行存款就是这些债务的总和。当银行办理储蓄业务时，货币以债务的形式被创造出来，<ref name="Bank of England Quarterly Bulletin 2014 Q1: Money creation in the modern economy">{{cite web|title=Money creation in the modern economy|url=https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/-/media/boe/files/quarterly-bulletin/2014/money-creation-in-the-modern-economy|accessdate=6 February 2014|publisher=Bank of England|archive-date=2022-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220423224134/https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/-/media/boe/files/quarterly-bulletin/2014/money-creation-in-the-modern-economy}}</ref>存款被储户取出就相当于银行偿还了这些债务，这些货币便从银行的资产负债表上消失。而一银行里的存款实际上是此前另一银行向客户提供的现金，长期来看，允许银行无限吸纳存款放出贷款，会大量创造货币，货币流入市场后抬升资产价值，最终要导致通货膨胀。这项法令是{{link-en|英国货币学派|currency school}}的胜利，该学院认为纸币的发行是[[通货膨胀|通货膨胀]]的罪魁祸首。

这项法令使得省级银行业公司合并成更大的银行，同时失去了发钞权。英格兰的民间钞票最终消失了，让[[英格兰银行|英格兰银行]]垄断了英格兰和威尔士的钞票发行权。英格兰和威尔士境内，最后一个自行发行钞票的银行是1921年的[[福克斯福勒银行|福克斯福勒银行]]（Fox，Fowler and Company）。<ref name="banknote-history">{{cite web|title=A brief history of banknotes|url=http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/banknotes/about/scottish_northernireland.htm|accessdate=31 October 2011|publisher=Bank of England|archive-date=2012-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120204061720/http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/banknotes/about/scottish_northernireland.htm}}</ref><ref name="fox-note">{{cite web|title=Fox, Fowler & Co. £5 note|url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/cm/f/fox,_fowler__co_%C2%A35_not.aspx|accessdate=31 October 2011|publisher=British Museum|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111002040119/http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/cm/f/fox,_fowler__co_%c2%a35_not.aspx|archive-date=2011-10-02|url-status=dead}}</ref>

一年后苏格兰实行的[[1845年银行法令|1845年银行法令]]则更加宽容，允许苏格兰的银行发行他们1845年流通量以上的货币，只要新增发行量有总部的黄金储备支持即可，银行兼并后也可以合并他们所发行的钞票。<ref>{{cite web|title=RBS History in 100 objects: Banknotes bill, 1844|url=https://www.rbs.com/heritage/rbs-history-in-100-objects/history-in-100-themes/turning-points/banknotes-bill-1844.html|accessdate=26 March 2018|website=RBS Heritage Hub|publisher=Royal Bank of Scotland|archive-date=2018-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180326203244/https://www.rbs.com/heritage/rbs-history-in-100-objects/history-in-100-themes/turning-points/banknotes-bill-1844.html}}</ref>

时至今日，[[蘇格蘭|蘇格蘭]]的三个商业银行和[[北爱尔兰|北爱尔兰]]的四个商业银行继续发行他们自己的[[英鎊紙幣|英鎊紙幣]]，但均受到[[英格兰银行|英格兰银行]]管制。<ref name="scot-ni">{{cite web|title=The Bank of England's Role in Regulating the Issue of Scottish and Northern Ireland Banknotes|url=http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/banknotes/about/scottish_northernireland.htm|accessdate=31 October 2011|publisher=Bank of England|archive-date=2012-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120204061720/http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/banknotes/about/scottish_northernireland.htm}}</ref>

